eholds, and 27 families residing in the CDP. The [[population density]] was 14.0 people per square mile (5.4/km\u00b2). There were 247 housing units at an average density of 24.7 per square mile (9.5/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the CDP was 97.86% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.71% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.71% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], and 0.71% from two or more races.\n\nThere were 79 households out of which 11.4% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 29.1% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 5.1% had a female householder with no husband present, and 65.8% were non-families. 40.5% of all households were made up of individuals and 11.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.77 and the average family size was 2.44.\n\nIn the CDP, the population was spread out with 8.6% under the age of 18, 4.3% from 18 to 24, 42.1% from 25 to 44, 35.0% from 45 to 64, and 10.0% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43 years. For every 100 females, there were 122.2 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 113.3 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the CDP was $25,000, and the median income for a family was $50,625. Males had a median income of $38,125 versus $17,813 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $31,618. There were 7.4% of families and 15.8% of the population living below the [[poverty line]], including 18.2% of under eighteens and 10.5% of those over 64.\n\n{{gallery\n|title=Images of Cooke City-Silver Gate, Montana\n|footer=\n|lines=3\n|width=150\n|File:2003-08-17 Miners Saloon in Cooke City, Montana.jpg|Miners Saloon, 2003\n|File:CookeCityMTJanuary2010.jpg|Looking East, January 2010\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Wikivoyage|Cooke City}}\n{{commons category|Cooke City, Montana}}\n{{Park County, Montana}}\n{{Tower Roosevelt}}\n{{Montana}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Park County, Montana]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Montana]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Cooke City-Silver Gate, Montana\n|settlement_type          = [[Census-designated place|CDP]]\n|image_skyline            = 2003-08-17 Entering Cooke City from the East.jpg\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = Entering Cooke City from the East\n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_map = Park_County_Montana_Incorporated_and_Unincorporated_areas_Cooke_City-Silver_Gate_Highlighted.svg\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = Location of Cooke City-Silver Gate, Montana\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|coordinates              = {{coord|45|1|3|N|109|56|19|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in Montana|County]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[Montana]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Park County, Montana|Park]]\n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             = \n|leader_name              = \n|leader_title1            = \n|leader_name1             = \n|unit_pref  =  Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = \n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 25.9\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 10.0\n|area_land_km2            = 25.9\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 10.0\n|area_water_km2           = 0.0\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.0\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              =2318.9 \n|elevation_ft             =7608 \n|population_total         = 140\n|population_as_of         = [[United States Census, 2000|2000]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_density_km2   = 5.4\n|population_density_sq_mi = 14.0\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|postal_code_type         = \n|postal_code              = \n|area_code                = [[Area code 406|406]]\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|timezone                 = [[Mountain Time Zone|Mountain (MST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -7\n|timezone_DST             = MDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -6\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 30-17359\n|blank1_name              = \n|blank1_info              = \n}}\n\n'''Cooke City-Silver Gate''' is a [[census-designated place]] (CDP) in [[Park County, Montana|Park County]], [[Montana]], United States. The population was 140 at the [[2000 United States Census|2000 census]].  It sits toward the northeast of [[Yellowstone National Park]] on a road remaining open during the winter connecting through Tower Junction to Mammoth and north to [[Livingston, Montana]].  During the summer the road opens eastward to connect to [[Red Lodge, Montana]] via the [[Beartooth Highway]] on a scenic route climbing to 10,947 feet in elevation through the Beartooth Mountains and across the Beartooth Plateau.  Its chief industry is tourism, which during the winter includes skiing and snowmobiling.\n\n==Geography==\nCooke City-Silver Gate is located at {{coord|45|1|3|N|109|56|19|W|type:city}} (45.017378, \u2212109.938599),<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref> at an elevation of 7,608 feet (2,318 m).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://geoinfo.msl.mt.gov/geography/geography_facts/elevation_of_montana_cities.aspx|title=Elevation of Montana Cities and Towns|last=|first=|date=|website=geoinfo.msl.mt.gov|publisher=|access-date=2016-11-27}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the CDP has a total area of {{convert|10.0|sqmi|km2}}, all of it land.\n\n==Climate==\n<div style=\"width:75%\">\nCooke City has a [[subarctic climate]] or [[subalpine climate]] due its extremely high elevation, at 7,608 feet (2,318 m), with only 2 months averaging above 50 degrees fahrenheit. Summers consist of mild to warm days with crisp cold mornings, and winters are long and very cold with many nights falling below zero. Snowfall is abundant, most of it falling between the months of October to May, but snow does occasionally fall in the months of June and September.{{Weather box \n|single line=  yes\n|location= 2 Miles West of Cooke City, Montana\n\n|Jan record high F =48\n|Feb record high F =54\n|Mar record high F =58\n|Apr record high F =72\n|May record high F =80\n|Jun record high F =88\n|Jul record high F =90\n|Aug record high F =88\n|Sep record high F =85\n|Oct record high F =76\n|Nov record high F =58\n|Dec record high F =47\n|year record high F=\n\n|Jan high F =24.3\n|Feb high F =30.1\n|Mar high F =37.1\n|Apr high F =44.4\n|May high F =54.2\n|Jun high F =64.5\n|Jul high F =74.0\n|Aug high F =72.2\n|Sep high F =62.4\n|Oct high F =48.6\n|Nov high F =32.1\n|Dec high F =23.6\n|year high F=\n\n|Jan mean F=14.3\n|Feb mean F=17.9\n|Mar mean F=24.4\n|Apr mean F=31.6\n|May mean F=40.8\n|Jun mean F=49.1\n|Jul mean F=56.2\n|Aug mean F=54.6\n|Sep mean F=46.1\n|Oct mean F=35.6\n|Nov mean F=22.3\n|Dec mean F=14.1\n\n|Jan low F = 4.3\n|Feb low F = 5.7\n|Mar low F =11.8\n|Apr low F =18.8\n|May low F =27.5\n|Jun low F =33.7\n|Jul low F =38.5\n|Aug low F =37.0\n|Sep low F =29.9\n|Oct low F =22.6\n|Nov low F =12.4\n|Dec low F = 4.6\n|year low F=\n\n|Jan record low F = \u221241\n|Feb record low F = \u221243\n|Mar record low F = \u221227\n|Apr record low F = \u221218\n|May record 